      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S FEARLESS (3) was the fastest winner on the program last time out, running away to score by 5.5 lengths (29.47) at Wentworth Park. Has good early burn and drawn to be prominent early off a low draw. Looks well placed and can measure up again. TEXAS BANDIT (1) turned in a plain run last time when fifth at Nowra over 520m behind Take A Break (30.57) in a Grade 4/5. Placed at his previous run. Has a win and two minor placings from three starts from this draw. One of the better hopes. CANYA PONGA (2) was out of the placings last time when seventh at Wentworth Park (30.53) but did record best time of the card when winning five back. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. Key runner on best form. TIN ROOF RUSTY (4) is a course and distance winner who must be respected.",
